Range figures based on WLTP standard. Your actual vehicle range will vary depending on the vehicle configuration, battery age and condition, driving style and operating, environmental and climate conditions. WLTP standard may be useful in comparing ranges among electric vehicles.

Tesla All-Wheel Drive uses multiple independent motors between the front and rear wheels for improved redundancy, each with only one moving part for minimal maintenance and maximum durability. Unlike traditional all-wheel drive systems, they digitally control torque for far better handling, performance and traction control.

Tesla All-Wheel Drive has two independent motors for improved redundancy, each with only one moving part for minimal maintenance and maximum durability. Unlike traditional all-wheel drive systems, they digitally control torque to the front and rear wheels for far better handling and traction control.

extra_copy.content: Specs displayed are US values. US model shown.
* Costs above include potential incentives and fuel savings of {SAVING_PRICE}.
All prices are shown without potential incentives or fuel savings of {SAVING_PRICE}.
* Prices shown include the {INCENTIVE_AMOUNT} {NAME_OF_INCENTIVE} and potential incentives and gas savings of {SAVING_PRICE}.
Prices shown without the {INCENTIVE_AMOUNT} {NAME_OF_INCENTIVE} and potential incentives and gas savings of {SAVING_PRICE}.
A 22-speaker, 960-watt audio system offers the best listening experience at home or on the road, and new microphones enable active noise cancelling.
The ultimate focus on driving: no stalks, no shifting. With a stalkless steering yoke, you can enjoy both the best car to drive, and the best car to be driven in.

Airflow and temperature are controlled entirely through the displays without any physical vents. On hot days, Cabin Overheat Protection ensures interiors always stay cool. In cold weather, pre-conditioning automatically warms the cabin and prepares the battery for maximum range.
Up to 10 teraflops of processing power enables in-car gaming on-par with today’s newest consoles via Tesla Arcade. Wireless controller compatibility allows gaming from any seat.

With 2200x1300 resolution, ultra-bright colors and exceptional responsiveness, the new centre display is an ideal touchscreen for entertainment and gaming anywhere. A second display in front of the driver shows various vehicle information, and a third display provides entertainment and controls for rear passengers.

Included with every new Tesla, Autopilot enables your car to steer, accelerate and brake automatically for other vehicles and pedestrians within its lane. There to assist with the most burdensome parts of driving, Autopilot works alongside features like emergency braking, collision warning and blind-spot monitoring.

Tesla All-Wheel Drive uses independent front and rear motors for improved performance and traction in all conditions, enabling lightning-fast response from the accelerator pedal. Unlike traditional engines, Tesla’s motors and powertrain require no scheduled maintenance for the lifetime of ownership.

Charge anywhere there is electricity. Most range used for daily driving can be topped off using the included Mobile Connector Bundle and an approved outlet, or upgrade to a Tesla Wall Connector for the best home charging experience. For long distance travel, Model S adds up to 200 miles of range in just 15 minutes on Tesla’s Supercharger network.

Our fully adaptive suspension responds to road conditions and driver input hundreds of time per second to give you better steering response, sporty handling and improved ride comfort, and the system will automatically lower itself based on speed and road type for improved efficiency and range. Like many Tesla systems, our adaptive suspension will continue to improve over time with over-the-air software updates.

Remotely control and monitor your Tesla with Phone Key keyless driving, range & charging status, climate control, live GPS location and more. You can even schedule service and monitor your entire Tesla ecosystem, including power flow from Powerwall or from Solar Roof and Solar Panels.

An exclusive protection feature called Sentry Mode continuously monitors the vehicle's surroundings when you leave your Tesla unattended. When activated, Sentry Mode arms and uses the vehicle's external cameras to detect and help protect against potential threats, similar to home alarm systems.

Live Camera, available with Premium Connectivity, lets you remotely view your car's surroundings while in park, and also honk, flash and talk through the car’s speaker. Live Camera is end-to-end encrypted and cannot be accessed by Tesla.

View Owners Manual for additional information.

The full Glass Roof gives passengers a brighter, more spacious experience and unobstructed views of the sky. Infrared and UV light is effectively blocked before entering the cabin, reducing heat and glare even when the sun is directly overhead.

A HEPA filtration system capable of stripping the outside air of pollen, bacteria, and pollution before they enter the cabin systematically scrubs the air inside the cabin to eliminate any trace of these particles, resulting in a system hundreds of times more efficient than standard automotive filters.

Access nearly all vehicle features on the expansive 17-inch touchscreen — designed to improve over time with regular software updates to provide new entertainment and safety features, added functionality and new user experiences. While driving, the 12-inch display behind the steering wheel displays nearby vehicles, speed limit signs, upcoming traffic lights, pedestrians, cyclists and road hazards.

Stay comfortable in cold weather with front and rear seat heaters, a heated steering wheel, wiper blade defrosters and washer nozzle heaters.Using the Tesla mobile app, you can activate cabin and battery pre-conditioning to automatically warm the cabin and prep the car’s battery for cold-weather driving to maximize range and efficiency.
Easily charge your smartphone, conveniently positioned in a centre-mounted holster for simple and secure docking

Automatic driving from motorway on-ramp to off-ramp includes automatic lane changes, Traffic-Aware Cruise Control with complete stopping and re-engagement, Autosteer, and overtaking slow cars in your lane.

While driving on the motorway, Automatic Lane Change will position your car in the optimal lane to prepare for merges and exits while overtaking slow cars. Drivers are given clear insight to upcoming lane changes as well as customisation to Auto Lane Change functionality.

Park with ease in both parallel and perpendicular parking spaces with a single button tap on the Centre Display. Model S will alert you to available parking spots by continuously monitoring the space around you.

Activated by the Tesla App, your parked car will come find you and even park or unpark itself in tight spaces. Smart Summon navigates complex parking situations while abiding by lane markings and stop signs, avoiding pedestrians and obstacles like traffic cones, rubbish bins and rogue shopping trolleys.
Tesla-designed silicon optimized for computer vision enables detailed, onscreen environment visualization and eventual Full Self-Driving Capability through over-the-air software updates.

Tesla designed Model S from the ground-up as an electric vehicle — each component, including batteries, motors and exterior aerodynamics are optimized to benefit from one another and create one of the most efficient, yet unbelievably powerful vehicles ever built.
The indicated Plaid top speed requires paid hardware upgrades.
Emergency lane departure avoidance and correction
Model S includes Navigation standard and a 1 year Premium Connectivity trial enabling:
Video Streaming, allowing access to content from Netflix, Youtube, Twitch, and more
Premium 22-speaker audio with Active Road Noise Reduction
Multi-device music and media over Bluetooth®
17” centre display, 12.3” driver’s display, and 8” second row display
Gaming computer with 10 teraflops of processing power
Heated seats for every passenger, heated steering and heated windshield
Custom driver profiles with automatic easy-entry and exit
Ultraviolet and infrared protection on all glass
28 ft³ of cargo space and secure front boot
Front centre console with sliding cup holders and storage
Second row stowable centre armrest with integrated storage and wireless charging
Automatic opening and closing rear liftgate
Auto dimming, power folding, heated side mirrors
Wireless and USB-C fast charging for every passenger
Video Streaming with access to Netflix, Youtube, Twitch, and more

Internet Browser
*New features that become available after delivery may be subject to additional charges.

Model S features 28 ft³ of cargo space, including a secure front boot, with space for 5 adults. The front boot can fit a full-size carry-on suitcase, and the rear seats can fold flat at the press of a button, opening up the rear cargo area and under-floor storage for maximum flexibility to fit any lifestyle.

Activated by the Tesla App, your parked car will come find you and even park or unpark itself in tight spaces. Smart Summon navigates complex parking situations while abiding by lane markings and stop signs, avoiding pedestrians and obstacles like traffic cones, rubbish bins and rogue shopping carts.

Park with ease in both parallel and perpendicular parking spaces with a single button tap on the Centre Display. Model S will alert you to available parking spots by continuously monitoring the space around you.

Automatic driving from motorway on-ramp to off-ramp includes automatic lane changes, Traffic-Aware Cruise Control with complete stopping and re-engagement, Autosteer, and overtaking slow cars in your lane.

While driving on the motorway, Automatic Lane Change will position your car in the optimal lane to prepare for merges and exits while overtaking slow cars. Drivers are given clear insight to upcoming lane changes as well as customisation to Auto Lane Change functionality.

Model S’ adaptive suspension reacts to road conditions and driver inputs hundreds of times per second to deliver exceptional ride quality and handling. The system also automatically adjusts ride height for greater comfort and to keep Model S in its most aerodynamic setting for maximum range.
Automatic steering, acceleration and braking on motorways
